üî§ What is Typography?
Typography refers to how text looks and behaves in your app. It includes font style,
 size, weight, color, letter spacing, and alignment. Good typography improves
  readability, accessibility, and visual appeal.


 | Concept               | Description                                 | Example                           |
 | --------------------- | ------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |
 | **Text Widget**       | The basic widget to display text            | `Text("Hello World")`             |
 | **TextStyle**         | Controls font size, color, weight, etc.     | `TextStyle(fontSize: 20)`         |
 | **Font Weight**       | Thickness of text                           | `FontWeight.bold`                 |
 | **Font Family**       | Type of font (Roboto, Montserrat, etc.)     | `fontFamily: 'Roboto'`            |
 | **Google Fonts**      | Custom fonts via the `google_fonts` package | `GoogleFonts.lato(...)`           |
 | **Theme Typography**  | Use global theme styles for consistency     | `Theme.of(context).textTheme`     |
 | **Overflow Handling** | Manage text overflow                        | `overflow: TextOverflow.ellipsis` |
 | **TextAlign**         | Align text left, right, center, justify     | `TextAlign.center`                |
